HEADWORD: Mancipate
<hw>Man"ci*pate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mancipatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>mancipare</ets> to sell. Cf.
<er>Emancipate</er>.]</ety> <def>To enslave; to bind; to restrict.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
